## Quick Start

### Option 1: Automated Installation (Recommended)

The easiest way to install is using the provided installation script:

```bash
# Verify checksums
sha256sum -c checksums.txt

# Make script executable
chmod +x scripts/install.sh

# Run installation
./scripts/install.sh
```

The script will:
1. Check prerequisites (kubectl, helm)
2. Create the namespace
3. Add the Helm repository
4. Install the Network Operator with your configuration
5. Apply the NicClusterPolicy
6. Wait for pods to be ready

### Option 2: Manual Installation

If you prefer manual control:

```bash
# Create namespace
kubectl create namespace {{ .Helm.Namespace }}

# Add Helm repository
helm repo add nvidia {{ .Script.HelmRepository }}
helm repo update

# Install Network Operator
helm install network-operator {{ .Script.HelmChart }} \
    --namespace {{ .Helm.Namespace }} \
    --values values.yaml \
    --create-namespace

# Apply NicClusterPolicy
kubectl apply -f manifests/nicclusterpolicy.yaml
```

